{
  "texts": [
    "Remarkably, this entire exploratory phase took just 12 months compared to 4-5 years of lead discovery in the conventional drug discovery process.",
    "DSP-1181 emerged as the eventual drug candidate.",
    "Zhavoronkov et al.",
    "developed inhibitors for the discoidin domain receptor family, member-1 (DDR1) kinase enzyme using the generative tensorial reinforcement learning (GEN-TRL) method (Zhavoronkov et al. 2019).",
    "They trained the models with compounds from the ZINC database and known DDR1 kinase inhibitors."
  ]
}